1
00:00:14,583 --> 00:00:15,833
What are you guys doing?

2
00:00:20,125 --> 00:00:21,833
You said you were taking me home.

3
00:00:25,125 --> 00:00:27,458
We aren't going to kill you.

4
00:00:32,250 --> 00:00:34,416
But I'm going to
do what I want first,

5
00:00:34,416 --> 00:00:35,833
then you can have the ring.

6
00:00:37,041 --> 00:00:49,041
Let go! I beg you, don't do this.
If you want money, I'll get it!

7
00:00:50,416 --> 00:00:51,416
I just want...

8
00:00:51,875 --> 00:00:53,166
I just want my ring back.

9
00:00:53,583 --> 00:00:55,375
I'll film us gang-raping you.

10
00:00:55,500 --> 00:00:56,500
I'm begging you.

11
00:00:57,083 --> 00:00:58,083
Begging?

12
00:00:58,500 --> 00:00:59,500
The more you beg,

13
00:01:00,363 --> 00:01:01,530
The more I want to do it.

14
00:01:06,197 --> 00:01:07,197
Let go!

15
00:01:20,863 --> 00:01:21,863
Let go!

16
00:01:21,947 --> 00:01:22,947
Let go of me!

17
00:01:24,738 --> 00:01:26,155
Let go of me!

18
00:01:44,697 --> 00:01:45,947
Hey, Nong.

19
00:01:47,947 --> 00:01:49,613
I'm gonna go to the bathroom
for a sec.

20
00:01:50,655 --> 00:01:51,655
Go ahead and keep at it.

21
00:02:27,410 --> 00:02:28,785
Let go of me.

22
00:02:37,410 --> 00:02:38,202
Hey.

23
00:02:38,868 --> 00:02:40,077
Why are you calling me right now?

24
00:02:40,077 --> 00:02:41,202
You're gonna ruin everything.

25
00:02:41,535 --> 00:02:42,410
Phi Nong,

26
00:02:42,410 --> 00:02:43,702
where are you?

27
00:02:43,702 --> 00:02:45,077
Can you take me to give birth?

28
00:02:45,077 --> 00:02:46,868
My stomach hurts so much right now.

29
00:02:48,160 --> 00:02:49,743
Can't someone else take you?

30
00:03:25,030 --> 00:03:26,489
Why did you do this?

31
00:03:27,947 --> 00:03:29,787
Aren't you afraid the person
you love will die?

32
00:03:34,530 --> 00:03:35,655
Stay out of it.

33
00:03:38,197 --> 00:03:39,655
You should stop worshiping love.

34
00:03:42,155 --> 00:03:43,614
True love doesn't fucking exist.

35
00:03:47,030 --> 00:03:48,364
Be careful.

36
00:03:49,072 --> 00:03:50,280
Whatever you do to others,

37
00:03:50,989 --> 00:03:52,572
you'll get right back.

38
00:04:10,074 --> 00:04:11,074
Perfect timing.

39
00:04:11,741 --> 00:04:12,866
Take this first.

40
00:04:14,533 --> 00:04:15,533
Why?

41
00:04:16,241 --> 00:04:17,741
You're really so kind to me.

42
00:04:18,283 --> 00:04:19,283
Did you take yours yet?

43
00:04:19,824 --> 00:04:20,824
I did.

44
00:04:21,324 --> 00:04:22,908
This is a brand new drug, man.

45
00:04:24,908 --> 00:04:26,009
It makes you high for a long time.

46
00:04:26,033 --> 00:04:27,033
Longer than before.

47
00:04:27,491 --> 00:04:29,033
A high you'll never come back from.

48
00:05:53,614 --> 00:05:55,114
You killed me.

49
00:05:56,489 --> 00:05:57,698
You think I'm awful?

50
00:05:59,448 --> 00:06:00,656
You're even worse than me.

51
00:06:01,823 --> 00:06:03,489
You were planning to take the money
and be with that bitch,

52
00:06:03,489 --> 00:06:04,823
your pregnant wife, right?

53
00:06:06,404 --> 00:06:07,404
Where are you, Nong?

54
00:06:07,487 --> 00:06:09,487
Don't forget to scam a lot
of money from him.

55
00:06:09,904 --> 00:06:11,737
I'm heavily pregnant now.

56
00:06:12,070 --> 00:06:13,320
I'm so excited.

57
00:06:21,779 --> 00:06:23,654
Shouldn't you take him to
the doctor first?

58
00:06:23,945 --> 00:06:25,612
Don't be so cold-blooded.

59
00:06:26,195 --> 00:06:28,070
That's a human life right there.

60
00:06:42,154 --> 00:06:44,779
If you love me, I'll love you back.

61
00:06:46,362 --> 00:06:48,029
But if you're awful to me,

62
00:06:49,529 --> 00:06:50,779
I'll be awful right back.

63
00:08:52,884 --> 00:08:54,051
Finally,

64
00:08:55,551 --> 00:08:57,092
I get to see you.

65
00:08:57,801 --> 00:08:59,134
Right, Phi Nat?

66
00:09:16,716 --> 00:09:17,507
Thank you.

67
00:11:45,227 --> 00:11:50,027
(One Year Later)

68
00:12:23,568 --> 00:12:24,568
Jae Chu,

69
00:12:25,568 --> 00:12:26,818
we should take a break to eat.

70
00:12:28,110 --> 00:12:29,777
I want to sweep here a bit more.

71
00:12:30,193 --> 00:12:32,402
I want to sweep it all up,

72
00:12:32,777 --> 00:12:34,402
so it's flawlessly clean.

73
00:12:39,235 --> 00:12:41,777
You can never sweep it all away.

74
00:12:46,480 --> 00:12:47,772
Falling leaves

75
00:12:49,147 --> 00:12:50,980
are like lives passing away.

76
00:12:55,230 --> 00:12:57,230
No one knows when they'll fall.

77
00:12:58,939 --> 00:13:00,439
It's like parting ways,

78
00:13:01,272 --> 00:13:02,730
with no advance warning.

79
00:13:04,689 --> 00:13:06,105
Are you telling me this?

80
00:13:10,230 --> 00:13:11,814
I'm telling myself.

81
00:13:13,480 --> 00:13:15,522
Realizing things when it's too late

82
00:13:17,105 --> 00:13:18,730
is the most painful thing.

83
00:13:30,522 --> 00:13:33,605
Missing him so much
when they're gone.

84
00:13:36,564 --> 00:13:37,564
Loving him the most

85
00:13:38,564 --> 00:13:40,439
when he can no longer hear it.

86
00:13:42,564 --> 00:13:44,605
I was too complacent with love.

87
00:13:50,850 --> 00:13:51,850
You know,

88
00:13:52,225 --> 00:13:53,642
for me,

89
00:13:54,183 --> 00:13:56,100
after dealing with the lawsuit,

90
00:13:57,100 --> 00:13:58,767
I still have a lot to fight through.

91
00:13:59,850 --> 00:14:02,475
I don't even know how
the results will turn out.

92
00:14:03,392 --> 00:14:04,642
But in the end,

93
00:14:05,600 --> 00:14:07,058
I have to accept it.

94
00:14:13,308 --> 00:14:15,058
Nat was very lucky

95
00:14:16,308 --> 00:14:17,350
to have you.

96
00:14:19,100 --> 00:14:20,600
Thank you so much

97
00:14:21,850 --> 00:14:23,058
for loving him.

98
00:14:29,267 --> 00:14:30,475
Nat is a good person.

99
00:14:33,350 --> 00:14:35,600
He craved love since he was a kid.

100
00:14:48,360 --> 00:14:49,360
Until one day,

101
00:14:51,151 --> 00:14:52,360
my wife found out

102
00:14:54,485 --> 00:14:55,901
that I like men.

103
00:14:59,610 --> 00:15:01,026
She saw us sleeping together.

104
00:15:06,610 --> 00:15:08,193
So she packed up my son...

105
00:15:09,901 --> 00:15:10,901
and left.

106
00:15:18,068 --> 00:15:19,068
Up until today,

107
00:15:20,360 --> 00:15:22,360
I haven't heard from them since.

108
00:15:23,985 --> 00:15:24,985
Including Nat,

109
00:15:26,026 --> 00:15:27,193
my son.

110
00:15:33,901 --> 00:15:35,776
Don't you think it's a small world?

111
00:15:38,735 --> 00:15:40,526
Bringing us to meet each other

112
00:15:43,026 --> 00:15:45,193
in these twisted relationships.

113
00:15:50,782 --> 00:15:51,782
I believe Nat

114
00:15:52,199 --> 00:15:53,324
was very lucky to have you.

115
00:15:58,074 --> 00:15:59,574
Even though when Nat was alive,

116
00:16:02,824 --> 00:16:04,104
you didn't pay attention to him,

117
00:16:07,990 --> 00:16:09,490
but when Nat passed away,

118
00:16:12,407 --> 00:16:14,032
you ended up missing him.

119
00:16:14,907 --> 00:16:15,949
That's still good.

120
00:16:36,240 --> 00:16:37,240
It's weird.

121
00:16:40,157 --> 00:16:41,157
We...

122
00:16:43,824 --> 00:16:45,407
we really are bound by karma.

123
00:17:38,913 --> 00:17:41,613
(The worst thing
about love is...)

124
00:17:41,813 --> 00:17:45,013
(Falling in love
when it's too late)

125
00:17:46,713 --> 00:17:50,213
(The End)
